The paper deals with the Restricted Isometry Property (RIP) of matrices, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The self Khatri-Rao product is a matrix factorization technique commonly used in data science (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions applications in activity detection and MIMO gain-estimation, which are topics in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
